<!-- conductor-kit begin -->
## conductor-kit workflow

This repository uses [conductor-kit](https://github.com/chanshin0/conductor-kit)
as the shared team workflow. One CLI (`conductor`), three agent adapters
(Claude Code / Codex CLI / Cursor). Core rule: **the CLI is deterministic;
agents do conversation + code editing, not orchestration.**

### Core contract

- Read `.conductor/CONVENTIONS.md` before editing any code. It is the single
  source of truth for branch / commit / validation rules in this repo.
- Session state lives in `.work/{ISSUE_KEY}.md`. Do not delete or rewrite
  status lines by hand — let `conductor` manage them.
- Every workflow step is a `conductor <cmd>` invocation. See
  `.codex/prompts/conductor-*.md` for the per-command playbooks.

### Plan-first gate (EnterPlanMode replacement)

Codex does not structurally block edits, so the convention is enforced by
the CLI + this prompt:

1. `conductor pick <KEY>` creates `.work/{KEY}.md` with `status: plan-draft`.
2. You (the agent) draft the plan, surface grey areas to the user, record
   their answers. **Do not call any Edit/Write tool on source files yet.**
3. The user says "approved". Run `conductor pick <KEY> --approve` — the
   status flips to `plan-approved`.
4. Only now may you edit code. `conductor ship` refuses to run unless
   status is `plan-approved` or `implementing`.

### Commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `conductor init` | Scaffold `.conductor/` in this repo (once). |
| `conductor where` | Snapshot current state, suggest next action. |
| `conductor pick <KEY>` | Jira → branch → transition → plan draft. |
| `conductor ship` | Validate → commit → push → MR → Jira ship comment. |
| `conductor land [<KEY>]` | After merge: Jira RESOLVE + cleanup. |
| `conductor recap [<KEY>]` | Post-merge Jira result comment. |
| `conductor draft "<desc>"` | Structured Jira issue draft. |
| `conductor tune "<feedback>"` | Route feedback to the right workflow file. |
| `conductor autopilot <KEY>` | Unattended pick → implement → ship loop. |

All are also available as `.codex/prompts/conductor-*.md` files.

### Authorship footer

All outputs (MR body, Jira comment, recap) end with a single line:

```
Generated via `conductor {COMMAND}` — agent Codex · conductor-kit v{CLI_VERSION} · user {USER}
```

The `Codex` label is hardcoded in every prompt file under `.codex/prompts/`.
Edit the `--agent "..."` value there if you want per-model attribution.

### Red lines

- Never `git commit --amend` or `git push --force`.
- Never `--no-verify` on commits.
- Never edit source files before `conductor pick <KEY> --approve`.
- Never re-run a failing check in a retry loop — surface the error and stop.
<!-- conductor-kit end -->
